HOUSE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 38
BY REPRESENTATIVE YOUNG
COMMENDATIONS: Commends Grambling State University on the occasion of the
centennial celebration of its world-renown Tiger Marching Band and recognizes its
contributions to music, education, culture, and Louisiana
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To commend Grambling State University on the celebration of the centennial of the World
3 Famed Tiger Marching Band and to recognize its outstanding contributions to music,
4 education, culture, and the state of Louisiana.
5 WHEREAS, Grambling State University celebrates the centennial of the World
6 Famed Tiger Marching Band in 2026 and marks one hundred years of demonstrating
7 excellence in musical performances; and
8 WHEREAS, the World Famed Tiger Marching Band was established in 1926 when
9 President Charles P. Adams requested Ralph Waldo Emerson Jones to organize a marching
10 band for the institution; Jones started the endeavor with only seventeen instruments and
11 created the foundation for a proud and enduring musical tradition; and
12 WHEREAS, the World Famed Tiger Marching Band has grown from humble
13 beginnings into one of the most distinguished collegiate marching bands in the nation and
14 has long served as a premier ambassador for Grambling State University and the state of
15 Louisiana; and
16 WHEREAS, renowned director Conrad Hutchinson, Jr., took the helm in 1952 and
17 elevated the band to new heights of precision, discipline, and artistry; under his leadership,
18 the band became widely known as "The Best Band in the Land"; and
19 WHEREAS, the World Famed Tiger Marching Band has earned national and
20 international recognition through its performances on some of the most prominent stages in
